  "language": "en",
  "full_transcript": "What's happening in the world right now? The wars, the conflicts, the anger everywhere? How are we supposed to find peace in all of this? That is exactly what Elder Bednar addressed in the last two general conferences. He reminded us of a powerful promise from Scripture. What promise? The Lord said in Doctrine and Covenant Section 101, Let your hearts be comforted. For all flesh is in mine hands. Be still and know that I am God. Be still. But how do we do that when everything around us is chaos? Elder Bednar taught that be still means more than just being quiet. It means to remember and rely upon the Lord and His power at all times. He promised that as we build the foundation of our lives on the rock of Jesus Christ, we can receive an individual and spiritual stillness of the soul. So the peace, it comes from within, from our connection to Christ. Elder Bednar testified, as we walk in the meekness of the Lord's Spirit, we will avoid and overcome pride and have peace in Him. In Him.",
